Recommended Uses For Product
Front door, Back door, Home, House, Hotel, Apartment, Office, Rental, etc.
  • 7-in-1 Smart Door Lock: Access your smart lock via Fingerprint + App + Web portal + Fobs +Code + eKey sharing + Mechanical key
  • App & Web Portal Control: You can control the smart lock via smartphone, remotely generate eKey and grant access, manage users, and view records in the app and website management system. The App & Web is free and can be used forever
  • Intelligent Management: With 50 fingerprints and 250+ multiple user codes, you can remotely generate and share one-time, permanent, scheduled, and recurring code with your house sitters and guests. Ideal for house, apartment, office, and hotel
  • Enhanced Security: The intelligent lock features auto-lock, one-touch locking, privacy mode, passage mode, and low battery alert, made with an anti-peeping and anti-hacking touchscreen keypad, keeping your home secure
  • Smart Home Integration: With the Veise G2 gateway(sold separately), you can remotely access your smart deadbolt and voice control with Alexa and Google Home, view real-time access logs, monitor smart lock status, etc
  • Veise smart door lock fits on most US standard left-handed and right-handed doors. It is easy to install with just a screwdriver. Veise offers at least 1-year warranty and lifetime online phone support from Monday to Friday 9 AM to 5 PM PST and 24/7 after-sales email service
  • NOTE: Do not use the keypad to change the Master Password before pairing the lock in the APP. Before pairing, you may need to touch the keypad to activate the lock. If the app does not find the lock or cannot connect, please reset the lock

      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Solid lock with lots of features - Worth the money!
      Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
      Color: Matte Black
      I purchased this to change the locks on our new home after closing, and installed it on June 30th. The installation was super simple - the instructions were clear, the included template was very helpful, and there were also video guides available as well if... See more
      I purchased this to change the locks on our new home after closing, and installed it on June 30th.

      The installation was super simple - the instructions were clear, the included template was very helpful, and there were also video guides available as well if needed (although I didn't need to use them).

      While the container/shell is made from a hard plastic, all of the moving parts and mechanisms are made of metal and are solid and durable. The lock feels extremely secure and reliable.

      The companion app that comes along with the lock is very well made, and while there are some weird translation issues (which is normal for products like these), everything works exactly as expected with no hiccups or bugs. There are TONS of features available - the lock is super customizable and everything can be managed from the app easily. New admins can be added very easily as well.

      In particular, I like that I can generate a new code on the door and set it to expire whenever, thus eliminating the need for hidden keys or anything like that. Whenever a handyman or friend/family member need to come by and we aren't here, I can just make them a new code and set it to expire the next day and never have to worry about them getting back into the front door again.

      I also really like that there's an auto-lock option - it's a great way to have peace of mind that the front door is always locked. You can set it to 5/10/15/30 seconds, or choose "custom" and set it to whatever timeframe you want (in seconds). For us, we have a 10 minute auto-lock set, which means that even if we forget after going in and out over and over again (moving and whatnot), we know that the door will always be locked after ten minutes.

      The fingerprint setup is a breeze, the RFID reader works reliably, everything is great - if I had to point out any one con, it would be with the keypad screen - it's kind of a pain to reliably wake up sometimes, and lags a bit when coming on. But that's the only real downside we have been able to find with it. Other than that, this lock is awesome, feature rich, reliable and well built. Worth the money.

      PS: Also, Veise's customer service is awesome. When I first got the lock, I realized that I only got 1 RFID scanner instead of 2, and after reaching out to them, they explained that other RFID cards can be used with the lock, and then refunded me back 30% of the total cost to cover the cost of purchasing new ones separately. All of this happened within 12 hours of me reaching out the first time. Nice job, Veise! :)

      Almost perfect ...
      Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2024
      Color: Satin Nickel
      The prior lock was name-brand and expensive, which started having random issues 6 months after purchase, and after a year it failed completely. Plus, it ate a lot of 9v batteries. This lock looked like the best replacement and had a large sale discount of 40%... See more
      The prior lock was name-brand and expensive, which started having random issues 6 months after purchase, and after a year it failed completely. Plus, it ate a lot of 9v batteries.

      This lock looked like the best replacement and had a large sale discount of 40% plus a $30 coupon, so we bought two on the same order. We did pay for the locks; we did not get it as a free item to review.

      It was exactly as it said, and the replacement was reasonably easy. But it did take me 3 hours due to the prior lock having been installed very poorly (a lot of damage to the door and frame), so I repaired that as best possible. Also, the inside and outside locks have a rubber insulator that comes off easily (and back on), which can be used as a guide to predrilling the holes. That's what I did, and it made it easy to be accurate.

      This lock works butter smooth and it has so many options for opening it.

      If you have multiple locks then you can set up the first one and there is an option to transfer the settings (the people with access) to the second lock through the app.

      The app uses Bluetooth, but they push the wifi option fairly heavily. We thought we had to buy the wifi to get phone connectivity, but decided to see if we needed the wifi box. if you are within about 6 feet of the door the Bluetooth option works fine.

      The app itself is ok, lots of setup options. But when there is an error (I tried to change the temporary code of a new person) and it fails with a simple "Failed" message. I tried again and then it failed with a more helpful message saying that I had to use the code once before changing it. Why can't it say that on the app at the time? There is little help nor description on the app itself about what an option does, and that is mostly fine but could be more helpful.

      What we liked most in the app was that the battery state is displayed, so no more guessing (the previous locks would work, until they didn't).

      The worst part of the lock is that the pictures on Amazon show a clear keypad, but it is covered in a darkly tinted glass. It looks nice, but we live in Texas and it is bright and sunny. We have a hard time seeing if the keypad is on, let alone the digits. Two of the people who posted videos showed that, but it is worse for us in the sun. The app issues are fairly minor since we mostly use the key-tags to open the doors.

      Overall, we are delighted and feel like we have great value compared to the name-brand locks we had.

      4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Good features, performs well, fingerprint is great, but device auto-locks even if door is open
      Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
      Color: Satin Nickel
      Overall I am happy with this smart lock, and would recommend it in spite of the flaw mentioned in the headline. The Veise smart lock was not difficult to install (it took 10-15 minutes), and the app has many features. All the features I have used function well,... See more
      Overall I am happy with this smart lock, and would recommend it in spite of the flaw mentioned in the headline.

      The Veise smart lock was not difficult to install (it took 10-15 minutes), and the app has many features. All the features I have used function well, especially the fingerprint reader. The one time I contacted tech support (via email), they responded in a few hours. I did not try to call the tech support number, so I cannot comment on that.

      The smart lock can pair with a wi-fi gateway so that you don't have to be near to the lock to control it, but like all smart lock gateways I have seen, it does not work with the most modern 5 GHz wi-fi signal, so if you also purchase the wi-fi gateway, make sure your home router supports the older 2.4 GHz signal (most routers do), and that the distance between the gateway and the door lock is within 32 feet (9.75 meters).

      The fingerprint reader works 99% of the time and unlocks in about one second (much better than the Bosma fingerprint reader I used to have!). When fingerprint reader didn't work, it was because my finger was wet (a problem with all fingerprint readers), I removed my finger too quickly, or I did not position my finger correctly.

      The reason I gave this smart lock 4 stars instead of 5: the app has a setting for auto-lock after a set amount of time that the user can choose, but the device automatically locks even if the door is open. If it auto-locked only when it was closed, I would give it 5 stars.

      After looking in the settings of the app and not finding a way to auto-lock only if the door is closed, I contacted the company asking if it was possible if this was possible. They said it was not. On a positive note, their tech support responded to my email within a few hours.

      I was going to ask Veise if they could perhaps implement this feature, because in their app DDlock I saw in the settings something that says, "Door Sensor" that might seem to let the app know if the door is open or closed. And then I thought the name of the app, DDlock, seemed strange to me, why isn't the name of the app "Veise"?

      So I did a little research, and there is another company that makes this lock and the app, and Veise simply puts their name on it and sells it. This is *not* a bad thing, but buyers should be aware that Veise has no control over the features (or the bugs!) of the smart lock or the app.
